### The project is structured into two main components

## The fetching component => fetching_deribit_data which is responsible for getting

    ## real time crypto currency prices and sending them to a rabbitmq queue.

## The persistence component => responsible for getting the data in the rabbitmq queue and inserting it to the db.

### To run the project you must have rabbitmq and postgres processes running on your local env

For that you can use the pre-configured docker-compose file which will bootstrap a postgres and rabbitmq instances

Then to run the project follow the commands below

1 - python3 -m venv venv (to create a virtual env)
2 - pip install -r requirements.txt
3 - python3 src/persistent_layer.py (to start listenning for incoming message)
3 - python3 src/fetching_deribit_data.py (to start publishing messages to the queue)
